00:16:57.840 --> 00:17:00.700 align:middle line:84%
So these are very
elementary practices.

00:17:00.700 --> 00:17:05.069 align:middle line:84%
But both of them have persisted
throughout history, probably

00:17:05.069 --> 00:17:06.900 align:middle line:90%
because they do something.

00:17:06.900 --> 00:17:08.780 align:middle line:84%
So from a psychological
perspective,

00:17:08.780 --> 00:17:12.000 align:middle line:84%
you can say, well, the act of
writing down what you want,

00:17:12.000 --> 00:17:14.910 align:middle line:84%
that will just
psychologically predispose you

00:17:14.910 --> 00:17:17.640 align:middle line:90%
to seeing that happening.

00:17:17.640 --> 00:17:20.490 align:middle line:84%
But the question is, whether it
actually does cause the world

00:17:20.490 --> 00:17:21.720 align:middle line:90%
to be different.

00:17:21.720 --> 00:17:23.910 align:middle line:84%
So that's kind of what we
study in the laboratory,

00:17:23.910 --> 00:17:25.680 align:middle line:84%
not so far these
magical practices,

00:17:25.680 --> 00:17:28.530 align:middle line:84%
but things like that where
you make very strong intention

00:17:28.530 --> 00:17:31.770 align:middle line:84%
and then you see whether it
changes something in the world.

00:17:31.770 --> 00:17:35.070 align:middle line:84%
Sigil magic is like
writing magic except that,

00:17:35.070 --> 00:17:38.670 align:middle line:84%
instead of writing something
down, you make a symbol for it

00:17:38.670 --> 00:17:41.860 align:middle line:84%
