00:29:19.660 --> 00:29:22.220 align:middle line:84%
you come back
again, again, again.

00:29:22.220 --> 00:29:26.530 align:middle line:90%


00:29:26.530 --> 00:29:28.870 align:middle line:84%
So a lot of people
say, I can't meditate.

00:29:28.870 --> 00:29:29.750 align:middle line:90%
And I say, why?

00:29:29.750 --> 00:29:30.910 align:middle line:84%
And they say, I don't
have enough time.

00:29:30.910 --> 00:29:32.230 align:middle line:84%
I say, well, how much
time do you stand

00:29:32.230 --> 00:29:33.640 align:middle line:90%
in line for a cup of coffee?

00:29:33.640 --> 00:29:37.180 align:middle line:84%
How much time do you spend
on social media on the web?

00:29:37.180 --> 00:29:39.490 align:middle line:84%
And I say, take
10 minutes of that

00:29:39.490 --> 00:29:43.410 align:middle line:90%
and turn it back to yourself.

00:29:43.410 --> 00:29:46.840 align:middle line:84%
And asking that
question, who am I?

00:29:46.840 --> 00:29:49.080 align:middle line:90%
Who am I really?

00:29:49.080 --> 00:29:51.810 align:middle line:84%
Who is it that's
living through me,

00:29:51.810 --> 00:29:55.210 align:middle line:90%
that's looking through my eyes?

00:29:55.210 --> 00:29:59.050 align:middle line:84%
>> Consciousness is so
obvious that for many people,

00:29:59.050 --> 00:30:01.360 align:middle line:84%
they don't even know what
you're talking about.

00:30:01.360 --> 00:30:04.360 align:middle line:84%
Most academics, and this is now
true everywhere in the world,

00:30:04.360 --> 00:30:07.780 align:middle line:84%
are taught according to
principles that have developed

00:30:07.780 --> 00:30:09.280 align:middle line:90%
within Western science.

00:30:09.280 --> 00:30:11.410 align:middle line:84%
That scientific
worldview is based

00:30:11.410 --> 00:30:14.800 align:middle line:84%
on a philosophical
set of assumptions

00:30:14.800 --> 00:30:16.610 align:middle line:90%
known as materialism.

00:30:16.610 --> 00:30:19.000 align:middle line:84%
So materialism, in
a nutshell, means

00:30:19.000 --> 00:30:22.960 align:middle line:84%
that everything is made
out of matter and energy,

00:30:22.960 --> 00:30:25.360 align:middle line:84%
including mind,
including consciousness,

00:30:25.360 --> 00:30:27.670 align:middle line:84%
including everything we
know about subjectivity.

00:30:27.670 --> 00:30:29.380 align:middle line:90%
That's the prevailing view.

00:30:29.380 --> 00:30:31.840 align:middle line:84%
So if you're
challenging that view,

00:30:31.840 --> 00:30:34.180 align:middle line:84%
you have the same problem
that you would in any domain

00:30:34.180 --> 00:30:36.740 align:middle line:84%
where you start
challenging the status quo.

00:30:36.740 --> 00:30:38.680 align:middle line:84%
The status quo doesn't
like to be challenged.

00:30:38.680 --> 00:30:41.740 align:middle line:84%
So it will push hard against
anything that challenges it

00:30:41.740 --> 00:30:43.990 align:middle line:90%
in an attempt to squash it.

00:30:43.990 --> 00:30:46.000 align:middle line:84%
This is the problem
with materialism.

00:30:46.000 --> 00:30:48.370 align:middle line:84%
Materialism doesn't know what
to do with consciousness.

00:30:48.370 --> 00:30:50.072 align:middle line:90%
So it sort of sets it aside.

00:30:50.072 --> 00:30:51.280 align:middle line:90%
We'll worry about that later.

00:30:51.280 --> 00:30:53.560 align:middle line:84%
Or it comes up with the
idea that somehow the brain

00:30:53.560 --> 00:30:56.710 align:middle line:84%
is complex enough that it
gives rise to experience, even

00:30:56.710 --> 00:31:00.820 align:middle line:84%
though nobody has any idea
how that could possibly be.

00:31:00.820 --> 00:31:03.580 align:middle line:84%
And we know that
materialism is pretty good,

00:31:03.580 --> 00:31:05.050 align:middle line:84%
because it gives
us the technology

00:31:05.050 --> 00:31:07.508 align:middle line:84%
to do this sort of an interview
with a special machine that

00:31:07.508 --> 00:31:08.950 align:middle line:90%
captures my image and so on.

00:31:08.950 --> 00:31:10.840 align:middle line:84%
So we don't want to
throw materialism away.

00:31:10.840 --> 00:31:11.883 align:middle line:90%
It's too good.

00:31:11.883 --> 00:31:13.300 align:middle line:84%
The question is,
is it good enough

00:31:13.300 --> 00:31:15.520 align:middle line:90%
to account for everything?

00:31:15.520 --> 00:31:17.920 align:middle line:84%
And here's where we
have the problem.

00:31:17.920 --> 00:31:21.220 align:middle line:84%
Clearly it is not accounting
for all of the experiences

00:31:21.220 --> 00:31:22.580 align:middle line:90%
that people talk about.

00:31:22.580 --> 00:31:24.820 align:middle line:10%
So what's missing?

00:31:24.820 --> 00:31:26.710 align:middle line:84%
When you look at the
esoteric traditions,

00:31:26.710 --> 00:31:28.990 align:middle line:84%
you immediately bump
up against what might

00:31:28.990 --> 00:31:30.670 align:middle line:90%
be thought of as proto science.

00:31:30.670 --> 00:31:34.030 align:middle line:84%
So alchemy, astrology,
and herbalism.

00:31:34.030 --> 00:31:36.490 align:middle line:84%
Alchemy was the
forerunner of chemistry.

00:31:36.490 --> 00:31:39.760 align:middle line:10%
Astrology is a forerunner of
astronomy, to some extent.

00:31:39.760 --> 00:31:42.790 align:middle line:84%
And herbalism is the
forerunner of pharmaceuticals.

00:31:42.790 --> 00:31:45.250 align:middle line:84%
What's interesting
is that historically,

00:31:45.250 --> 00:31:48.340 align:middle line:84%
all three of those
proto sciences

00:31:48.340 --> 00:31:52.020 align:middle line:84%
also had a fourth element in it,
the element of consciousness,

00:31:52.020 --> 00:31:53.890 align:middle line:84%
where the practitioner
of alchemy

00:31:53.890 --> 00:31:56.710 align:middle line:84%
or the practitioner of
astrology or herbalism

00:31:56.710 --> 00:31:59.290 align:middle line:84%
knew that their intention was
a very important component

00:31:59.290 --> 00:32:00.820 align:middle line:90%
of what they were doing.

00:32:00.820 --> 00:32:02.620 align:middle line:90%
This is true in each case.

00:32:02.620 --> 00:32:05.440 align:middle line:10%
And yet, science has
stripped that out.

00:32:05.440 --> 00:32:07.570 align:middle line:84%
You don't consider
when you take a pill

00:32:07.570 --> 00:32:10.090 align:middle line:84%
that your intention is
important, except maybe

00:32:10.090 --> 00:32:10.945 align:middle line:90%
as a placebo.

00:32:10.945 --> 00:32:12.820 align:middle line:84%
But certainly when you're
preparing something

00:32:12.820 --> 00:32:17.120 align:middle line:84%
like metals or in chemistry,
people don't think about that.

00:32:17.120 --> 00:32:19.010 align:middle line:84%
But that was part of
the original idea.

00:32:19.010 --> 00:32:21.070 align:middle line:84%
And so I think what
is happening now

00:32:21.070 --> 00:32:22.780 align:middle line:84%
is that science is
slowly beginning

00:32:22.780 --> 00:32:25.870 align:middle line:84%
to mature to the point where
it sees that the intention

00:32:25.870 --> 00:32:28.300 align:middle line:84%
and consciousness
of the scientist

00:32:28.300 --> 00:32:32.720 align:middle line:84%
is as important an ingredient as
it was in alchemy and astrology

00:32:32.720 --> 00:32:34.420 align:middle line:90%
and so on.

00:32:34.420 --> 00:32:37.390 align:middle line:10%
So I looked in detail at
the esoteric traditions,

00:32:37.390 --> 00:32:39.370 align:middle line:10%
all the way back
from shamanism to

00:32:39.370 --> 00:32:42.370 align:middle line:10%
Pythagoras, Eastern
traditions, all the way up

00:32:42.370 --> 00:32:43.870 align:middle line:10%
to the present time.

00:32:43.870 --> 00:32:47.830 align:middle line:84%
And you find that there's a
similar thread of thought.

00:32:47.830 --> 00:32:51.490 align:middle line:84%
And basically, they're saying
that a better model of reality

00:32:51.490 --> 00:32:55.300 align:middle line:84%
is idealism, that everything
is made out of mind,

00:32:55.300 --> 00:32:56.140 align:middle line:90%
including matter.

00:32:56.140 --> 00:32:59.430 align:middle line:90%


00:32:59.430 --> 00:33:01.410 align:middle line:90%
That solves, at one stroke--

00:33:01.410 --> 00:33:05.220 align:middle line:84%
if that method is correct, if
that assumption is correct,

00:33:05.220 --> 00:33:08.160 align:middle line:84%
it solves all of the puzzles
about psychic phenomena

00:33:08.160 --> 00:33:10.230 align:middle line:84%
and mysticism and
all of that stuff.

00:33:10.230 --> 00:33:13.140 align:middle line:84%
So now consciousness
came here first.

00:33:13.140 --> 00:33:15.540 align:middle line:84%
And so the scientific
challenge is,

00:33:15.540 --> 00:33:18.300 align:middle line:84%
how do we get from
pure awareness

00:33:18.300 --> 00:33:21.620 align:middle line:84%
to emerge into space and
time and matter and energy?

00:33:21.620 --> 00:33:22.420 align:middle line:90%
How do we do that?

00:33:22.420 --> 00:33:25.080 align:middle line:84%
Well, there are lots of people
working on that very problem.

00:33:25.080 --> 00:33:28.260 align:middle line:84%
How do you emerge out
of something that seems

00:33:28.260 --> 00:33:32.880 align:middle line:90%
non-physical into physicality?

00:33:32.880 --> 00:33:36.780 align:middle line:84%
>> When we recognize that every
single material thing at its

00:33:36.780 --> 00:33:40.530 align:middle line:84%
core is energy and
everything is vibrating,

00:33:40.530 --> 00:33:44.880 align:middle line:84%
then you can get a feeling for
this nature of existence that

00:33:44.880 --> 00:33:49.530 align:middle line:84%
is not as materially
real as we tend to think.

00:33:49.530 --> 00:33:51.330 align:middle line:84%
And to me, that's what
it's really about,

00:33:51.330 --> 00:33:53.100 align:middle line:84%
that the nature
of reality itself

00:33:53.100 --> 00:33:56.560 align:middle line:84%
is consciousness
looking at itself.

00:33:56.560 --> 00:33:59.110 align:middle line:90%
It's basically a feedback loop.

00:33:59.110 --> 00:34:02.480 align:middle line:84%
So we're looking at the outside
world realizing, wait a minute.

00:34:02.480 --> 00:34:04.840 align:middle line:84%
Maybe what we're seeing
is consciousness itself.

00:34:04.840 --> 00:34:07.960 align:middle line:84%
And it starts to seem,
that is the case.

00:34:07.960 --> 00:34:10.540 align:middle line:84%
So we're at a time
in our history

00:34:10.540 --> 00:34:13.510 align:middle line:84%
where quantum physics
is challenging all of us

00:34:13.510 --> 00:34:16.300 align:middle line:84%
to take a whole new look at
the way we see the world.

00:34:16.300 --> 00:34:19.340 align:middle line:90%


00:34:19.340 --> 00:34:22.699 align:middle line:84%
>> Some scientists who strongly
resist this are of the opinion

00:34:22.699 --> 00:34:26.652 align:middle line:84%
that we basically understand
how reality works.

00:34:26.652 --> 00:34:28.610 align:middle line:84%
There's a couple of things
left over to mop up,

00:34:28.610 --> 00:34:30.230 align:middle line:90%
but we kind of got it.

00:34:30.230 --> 00:34:32.810 align:middle line:84%
I think that view
is so arrogant.

00:34:32.810 --> 00:34:34.820 align:middle line:84%
And even just from a
historical perspective,

00:34:34.820 --> 00:34:38.060 align:middle line:84%
you see about every 20 years
some prominent scientist

00:34:38.060 --> 00:34:39.978 align:middle line:84%
saying, well, it's
all wrapped up.

00:34:39.978 --> 00:34:42.020 align:middle line:84%
We just have these one or
two things left to fix,

00:34:42.020 --> 00:34:44.230 align:middle line:90%
and then we got it all.

00:34:44.230 --> 00:34:46.929 align:middle line:84%
It's just stupid
from my perspective.

00:34:46.929 --> 00:34:48.520 align:middle line:90%
Science is young.

00:34:48.520 --> 00:34:50.469 align:middle line:84%
And we have far
more things that we

00:34:50.469 --> 00:34:52.909 align:middle line:84%
don't understand
fundamentally at all

00:34:52.909 --> 00:34:55.360 align:middle line:84%
than we do understand
a little bit.

00:34:55.360 --> 00:34:57.670 align:middle line:84%
And that's one of the
fears that arises then.

00:34:57.670 --> 00:35:00.550 align:middle line:84%
Saying, well, I've spent my
entire career as a professor,

00:35:00.550 --> 00:35:02.950 align:middle line:84%
professing certain ideas
about the way things work.

00:35:02.950 --> 00:35:05.840 align:middle line:84%
And you're coming to me
and saying, actually,

00:35:05.840 --> 00:35:07.870 align:middle line:84%
you didn't understand
that at all.

00:35:07.870 --> 00:35:09.455 align:middle line:90%
Well, that's frightening.

00:35:09.455 --> 00:35:11.080 align:middle line:84%
I mean, no one wants
to think that they

00:35:11.080 --> 00:35:12.970 align:middle line:90%
don't know what's going on.

00:35:12.970 --> 00:35:15.400 align:middle line:84%
This is one of the reasons
why the Institute of Noetic

00:35:15.400 --> 00:35:19.390 align:middle line:84%
Sciences is a private,
non-profit institution.

00:35:19.390 --> 00:35:21.430 align:middle line:84%
Because we're looking
at things that do

00:35:21.430 --> 00:35:23.140 align:middle line:90%
challenge the status quo.

00:35:23.140 --> 00:35:26.300 align:middle line:84%
You can't do this in
the academic world.

00:35:26.300 --> 00:35:30.320 align:middle line:84%
We were among the first to
support research on meditation,

00:35:30.320 --> 00:35:34.040 align:middle line:84%
research on the positive
psychological and health

00:35:34.040 --> 00:35:36.530 align:middle line:84%
consequences of things
like gratefulness

00:35:36.530 --> 00:35:39.860 align:middle line:84%
and forgiveness, mind-body
connections in health

00:35:39.860 --> 00:35:40.980 align:middle line:90%
and so on.

00:35:40.980 --> 00:35:42.692 align:middle line:84%
We were supporting
these kinds of ideas

00:35:42.692 --> 00:35:44.150 align:middle line:84%
at a time when they
were considered

00:35:44.150 --> 00:35:48.470 align:middle line:90%
laughable and extremely risky.

00:35:48.470 --> 00:35:52.040 align:middle line:84%
So if somebody wants to
live a comfortable life,

00:35:52.040 --> 00:35:55.850 align:middle line:84%
the easiest thing to do is to
go along with the flow, always.

00:35:55.850 --> 00:35:57.740 align:middle line:84%
And if someone has
a family and they

00:35:57.740 --> 00:36:00.290 align:middle line:84%
have children to
support and all that,

00:36:00.290 --> 00:36:02.510 align:middle line:84%
it is actually the
responsible thing

00:36:02.510 --> 00:36:04.340 align:middle line:84%
for the sake of the
rest of the family,

00:36:04.340 --> 00:36:08.110 align:middle line:90%
to not challenge the status quo.

00:36:08.110 --> 00:36:10.690 align:middle line:84%
We live in a society
that is constantly

00:36:10.690 --> 00:36:13.030 align:middle line:90%
pushing certain ways to be.

00:36:13.030 --> 00:36:14.890 align:middle line:84%
And among other
things, we are not

00:36:14.890 --> 00:36:18.400 align:middle line:84%
taught to think for ourselves
or to think critically

00:36:18.400 --> 00:36:24.200 align:middle line:84%
or to question our own motives
and our unconscious desires.

00:36:24.200 --> 00:36:26.340 align:middle line:90%
It requires taking risk.

00:36:26.340 --> 00:36:27.140 align:middle line:90%
But so what?

00:36:27.140 --> 00:36:29.840 align:middle line:90%
Life is a risk.

00:36:29.840 --> 00:36:33.960 align:middle line:84%
>> It's a challenge to face
up to a lot of opposition.

00:36:33.960 --> 00:36:36.150 align:middle line:84%
Collectively, there
is a driving force

00:36:36.150 --> 00:36:39.030 align:middle line:84%
that tends to move events
in a certain direction.

00:36:39.030 --> 00:36:40.920 align:middle line:84%
And if you've ever
gone up against it,

00:36:40.920 --> 00:36:44.073 align:middle line:84%
it can feel like a
fish swimming upstream.

00:36:44.073 --> 00:36:46.240 align:middle line:84%
Like you're going in one
direction and everyone else

00:36:46.240 --> 00:36:49.420 align:middle line:90%
is going somewhere else.

00:36:49.420 --> 00:36:51.600 align:middle line:84%
The more you go into this
practice of meditation

00:36:51.600 --> 00:36:54.780 align:middle line:84%
and the more you recognize
that you are a consciousness,

00:36:54.780 --> 00:36:56.550 align:middle line:84%
I would not say it
becomes easy, but it

00:36:56.550 --> 00:37:00.180 align:middle line:84%
becomes possible to
stand up to society,

00:37:00.180 --> 00:37:02.580 align:middle line:84%
to your parents, or
your internalization

00:37:02.580 --> 00:37:04.853 align:middle line:84%
of what you think your
parents want for you.

00:37:04.853 --> 00:37:07.020 align:middle line:84%
And the funny thing about
doing this quantum jumping

00:37:07.020 --> 00:37:10.950 align:middle line:84%
is, often you'll notice that
people seem like they change.

00:37:10.950 --> 00:37:12.840 align:middle line:84%
And where there had
been opposition,

00:37:12.840 --> 00:37:15.000 align:middle line:90%
now there's support.

00:37:15.000 --> 00:37:18.120 align:middle line:84%
>> I know a lot of people have
a struggle with their parents

00:37:18.120 --> 00:37:21.050 align:middle line:84%
because their parents aren't
supporting them in doing what

00:37:21.050 --> 00:37:21.850 align:middle line:90%
they love.

00:37:21.850 --> 00:37:23.850 align:middle line:84%
Their parents have
a different idea.

00:37:23.850 --> 00:37:25.080 align:middle line:90%
My father certainly did.

00:37:25.080 --> 00:37:27.180 align:middle line:90%
He was concerned for me.

00:37:27.180 --> 00:37:31.560 align:middle line:84%
Going into theater and music
did not seem like a good idea.

00:37:31.560 --> 00:37:33.750 align:middle line:84%
He wanted me to
go into business.

00:37:33.750 --> 00:37:36.240 align:middle line:84%
And I realized, I
got deep somehow,

00:37:36.240 --> 00:37:39.270 align:middle line:84%
that it doesn't do any good
to do what your parents want.

00:37:39.270 --> 00:37:40.720 align:middle line:90%
You have to do what you want.

00:37:40.720 --> 00:37:43.240 align:middle line:84%
But it doesn't do any
good to fight them either.

00:37:43.240 --> 00:37:46.020 align:middle line:90%
So I just ignored my father.

00:37:46.020 --> 00:37:48.630 align:middle line:90%
He complained to my brother.

00:37:48.630 --> 00:37:51.000 align:middle line:84%
He said, Mark is so
slippery, you know?

00:37:51.000 --> 00:37:52.680 align:middle line:90%
He just blows me off.

00:37:52.680 --> 00:37:53.760 align:middle line:90%
He doesn't fight me.

00:37:53.760 --> 00:37:55.770 align:middle line:90%
He doesn't object.

00:37:55.770 --> 00:37:59.880 align:middle line:90%
He just sort of slides away.

00:37:59.880 --> 00:38:03.270 align:middle line:84%
>> One of the requisites of
change is that you have to deal

00:38:03.270 --> 00:38:08.340 align:middle line:84%
with objections at home or in
whatever environment you go

00:38:08.340 --> 00:38:10.170 align:middle line:90%
back to.

00:38:10.170 --> 00:38:14.130 align:middle line:84%
So let's say you want to do a
lot of work on your identity.

00:38:14.130 --> 00:38:16.110 align:middle line:10%
All of a sudden, you're
awakening your ability

00:38:16.110 --> 00:38:18.210 align:middle line:10%
to cause changes in
accordance with your will.

00:38:18.210 --> 00:38:20.640 align:middle line:84%
You're starting to tap into
feelings of worthiness,

00:38:20.640 --> 00:38:22.020 align:middle line:90%
starting to feel strong.

00:38:22.020 --> 00:38:23.460 align:middle line:90%
But then you go home.

00:38:23.460 --> 00:38:25.880 align:middle line:84%
And these people
have a picture of you

00:38:25.880 --> 00:38:29.820 align:middle line:84%
that is not the picture that
you're working to become.

00:38:29.820 --> 00:38:31.180 align:middle line:90%
It's the old you.

00:38:31.180 --> 00:38:34.970 align:middle line:10%
And it may not even be accurate,
but it's their image of you.

00:38:34.970 --> 00:38:37.020 align:middle line:84%
And I think you
can say, hey, look.

00:38:37.020 --> 00:38:38.230 align:middle line:90%
I'm really working on this.

00:38:38.230 --> 00:38:39.855 align:middle line:84%
This is really, really
important to me.

00:38:39.855 --> 00:38:41.310 align:middle line:84%
This is who I'm
working to become.

00:38:41.310 --> 00:38:44.970 align:middle line:84%
I'd really love to
count on your support.

00:38:44.970 --> 00:38:47.080 align:middle line:84%
I know you're just kidding,
but I'd appreciate it

00:38:47.080 --> 00:38:49.330 align:middle line:90%
if you just cut it out for now.

00:38:49.330 --> 00:38:51.250 align:middle line:84%
And if you don't
respect that, I'm

00:38:51.250 --> 00:38:52.670 align:middle line:84%
going to have to
ask you to leave.

00:38:52.670 --> 00:38:54.337 align:middle line:84%
I'm just going to not
hang out with you.

00:38:54.337 --> 00:38:57.490 align:middle line:84%
I don't want someone else
to sabotage right now.

00:38:57.490 --> 00:38:59.780 align:middle line:90%
It might mean not responding.

00:38:59.780 --> 00:39:03.350 align:middle line:84%
It might mean hardening
yourself psychologically to be

00:39:03.350 --> 00:39:04.470 align:middle line:90%
able to handle it.

00:39:04.470 --> 00:39:06.750 align:middle line:84%
You can't always ask
other people to change.

00:39:06.750 --> 00:39:09.080 align:middle line:90%
Most of the time, they won't.

00:39:09.080 --> 00:39:11.690 align:middle line:84%
>> Not everybody
really wants help.

00:39:11.690 --> 00:39:15.290 align:middle line:84%
One thing I've learned
the hard way in this field

00:39:15.290 --> 00:39:17.600 align:middle line:84%
is, some people just
want to complain.

00:39:17.600 --> 00:39:21.710 align:middle line:84%
Some people want to
complain about the problem

00:39:21.710 --> 00:39:24.480 align:middle line:84%
and don't actually want
to resolve the problem.

00:39:24.480 --> 00:39:27.020 align:middle line:84%
And we've all had friends
or heard of somebody

00:39:27.020 --> 00:39:29.150 align:middle line:84%
that, they always seem
to find themselves

00:39:29.150 --> 00:39:31.682 align:middle line:84%
in the same type of scenario,
the same type of issue,

00:39:31.682 --> 00:39:33.890 align:middle line:84%
the same relationship, even
though with three or four

00:39:33.890 --> 00:39:35.752 align:middle line:84%
different people,
it's the same story.

00:39:35.752 --> 00:39:38.210 align:middle line:84%
It's like, look, you're always
attracting people like this.

00:39:38.210 --> 00:39:40.730 align:middle line:84%
Something is going on
with you internally

00:39:40.730 --> 00:39:42.950 align:middle line:84%
that you need to
resolve in order to move

00:39:42.950 --> 00:39:44.730 align:middle line:90%
on to the next level of life.

00:39:44.730 --> 00:39:48.040 align:middle line:84%
But not everybody
really wants to change.

00:39:48.040 --> 00:39:53.380 align:middle line:84%
It's very possible, but you also
must believe, have the faith

00:39:53.380 --> 00:39:54.190 align:middle line:90%
that it's possible.

00:39:54.190 --> 00:39:57.160 align:middle line:84%
And then just align yourself
with the people out there

00:39:57.160 --> 00:40:00.153 align:middle line:84%
that are also on the same
wavelength, so to speak.

00:40:00.153 --> 00:40:01.570 align:middle line:84%
And stay away from
the people that

00:40:01.570 --> 00:40:03.460 align:middle line:90%
are going to drag you down.

00:40:03.460 --> 00:40:05.800 align:middle line:84%
And we really need
to dictate and decide

00:40:05.800 --> 00:40:08.260 align:middle line:84%
up front how much time
we are willing to put

00:40:08.260 --> 00:40:11.620 align:middle line:84%
into those friendships or those
partnerships or those people.

00:40:11.620 --> 00:40:13.730 align:middle line:84%
And you have to think
about that in advance.

00:40:13.730 --> 00:40:16.420 align:middle line:84%
You can't just let it work out
however it's going to work out.

00:40:16.420 --> 00:40:18.170 align:middle line:84%
Because it will suck
up all of your energy

00:40:18.170 --> 00:40:22.570 align:middle line:84%
and you have to keep your energy
intact and focus for the things

00:40:22.570 --> 00:40:24.250 align:middle line:84%
that are really most
important to you.

00:40:24.250 --> 00:40:26.600 align:middle line:84%
>> One of the best things
you can do is just set a good

00:40:26.600 --> 00:40:27.400 align:middle line:90%
example.

00:40:27.400 --> 00:40:30.680 align:middle line:84%
And it's hard to help people
unless they ask for help.

00:40:30.680 --> 00:40:34.420 align:middle line:84%
So I don't recommend pushing
your values on someone else

00:40:34.420 --> 00:40:37.030 align:middle line:84%
unless they ask you,
like, what are you doing?

00:40:37.030 --> 00:40:41.320 align:middle line:84%
Otherwise probably that's
not their path right now.

00:40:41.320 --> 00:40:45.250 align:middle line:84%
You need to be your own
example of being the change

00:40:45.250 --> 00:40:48.010 align:middle line:84%
that you wish to
see in the world.

00:40:48.010 --> 00:40:50.780 align:middle line:84%
>> Everything happens
exactly as it should.

00:40:50.780 --> 00:40:52.480 align:middle line:84%
And then it's a
very unique place

00:40:52.480 --> 00:40:56.050 align:middle line:84%
to be able to be grateful
for where we are today,

00:40:56.050 --> 00:40:57.688 align:middle line:84%
grateful for what
you have, grateful

00:40:57.688 --> 00:40:59.230 align:middle line:84%
for what we've
accomplished, grateful

00:40:59.230 --> 00:41:00.640 align:middle line:90%
for all your experiences.

00:41:00.640 --> 00:41:04.030 align:middle line:84%
Yet at the same
time, be able to want

00:41:04.030 --> 00:41:09.180 align:middle line:84%
or expect or allow more
to continue to come in.

00:41:09.180 --> 00:41:13.830 align:middle line:84%
>> Life can be very complicated
and difficult when people are

00:41:13.830 --> 00:41:15.570 align:middle line:90%
grasping all the time.

00:41:15.570 --> 00:41:17.190 align:middle line:84%
And I think when
we're constantly

00:41:17.190 --> 00:41:21.600 align:middle line:84%
achieving something new instead
of celebrating what is, we

00:41:21.600 --> 00:41:24.060 align:middle line:90%
become less and less satisfied.

00:41:24.060 --> 00:41:25.320 align:middle line:90%
It's like a drug.

00:41:25.320 --> 00:41:26.430 align:middle line:90%
Money is a drug.

00:41:26.430 --> 00:41:27.420 align:middle line:90%
Sex is a drug.

00:41:27.420 --> 00:41:28.680 align:middle line:90%
Shopping is a drug.

00:41:28.680 --> 00:41:31.694 align:middle line:84%
It's a bottomless pit,
trying to satisfy ourselves.

00:41:31.694 --> 00:41:35.410 align:middle line:90%


00:41:35.410 --> 00:41:38.200 align:middle line:84%
>> This culture, especially
in the United States,

00:41:38.200 --> 00:41:42.970 align:middle line:84%
this society really has
this succeed, excel.

00:41:42.970 --> 00:41:44.830 align:middle line:90%
It's the consumer mentality.

00:41:44.830 --> 00:41:46.910 align:middle line:84%
Do more, buy more,
be more, have more.

00:41:46.910 --> 00:41:48.700 align:middle line:84%
A bigger house,
bigger car, fill up

00:41:48.700 --> 00:41:51.580 align:middle line:84%
a garage full of 10,000
rolls of toilet paper,

00:41:51.580 --> 00:41:53.120 align:middle line:90%
and buy as much as you can.

00:41:53.120 --> 00:41:55.420 align:middle line:84%
And people have garages and
storages and more stuff.

00:41:55.420 --> 00:41:56.500 align:middle line:84%
And they have so
much stuff, they

00:41:56.500 --> 00:41:57.370 align:middle line:90%
can't even store the stuff.

00:41:57.370 --> 00:41:59.995 align:middle line:84%
They have to pay for a place to
store the stuff that they can't

00:41:59.995 --> 00:42:01.270 align:middle line:90%
even store at their own house.

00:42:01.270 --> 00:42:04.570 align:middle line:90%
And this is the way people live.

00:42:04.570 --> 00:42:06.760 align:middle line:84%
Just because you
have more externally,

00:42:06.760 --> 00:42:10.810 align:middle line:84%
it doesn't always correlate
to being internally fulfilled.

00:42:10.810 --> 00:42:13.180 align:middle line:84%
Those are two completely
different things.

00:42:13.180 --> 00:42:17.170 align:middle line:84%
And external, your environment,
the house, the cars, the stuff

00:42:17.170 --> 00:42:18.560 align:middle line:90%
is never fulfilling.

00:42:18.560 --> 00:42:19.670 align:middle line:90%
Its short term.

00:42:19.670 --> 00:42:20.760 align:middle line:90%
You get the fulfillment.

00:42:20.760 --> 00:42:21.560 align:middle line:90%
You buy it.

00:42:21.560 --> 00:42:22.360 align:middle line:90%
You have it.

00:42:22.360 --> 00:42:23.500 align:middle line:90%
You play with it.

00:42:23.500 --> 00:42:25.790 align:middle line:84%
And you get the short term,
instant gratification type

00:42:25.790 --> 00:42:26.590 align:middle line:90%
of thing.

00:42:26.590 --> 00:42:28.630 align:middle line:84%
But just like a
child with a new toy,

00:42:28.630 --> 00:42:30.840 align:middle line:84%
you run out of motivation
after a little while.

00:42:30.840 --> 00:42:32.770 align:middle line:90%
And you're on to the next toy.

00:42:32.770 --> 00:42:35.620 align:middle line:84%
>> The ultimate insanity
of it was the '80s.

00:42:35.620 --> 00:42:40.000 align:middle line:84%
I remember a guy, he actually
had a bumper sticker saying,

00:42:40.000 --> 00:42:42.820 align:middle line:84%
whoever dies with
the most toys wins.

00:42:42.820 --> 00:42:45.760 align:middle line:90%
And I remember thinking, wrong.

00:42:45.760 --> 00:42:47.290 align:middle line:90%
That's not true.

00:42:47.290 --> 00:42:49.840 align:middle line:84%
It's not about amassing
more and more toys.

00:42:49.840 --> 00:42:51.670 align:middle line:84%
True, when you're
poor, there's a lot

00:42:51.670 --> 00:42:53.500 align:middle line:84%
of stress about
paying the bills.

00:42:53.500 --> 00:42:56.710 align:middle line:84%
But going purely
for material success

00:42:56.710 --> 00:43:00.690 align:middle line:84%
will never achieve
the satisfaction

00:43:00.690 --> 00:43:03.170 align:middle line:84%
that we're all
looking for in life.

00:43:03.170 --> 00:43:06.640 align:middle line:84%
You've got to be careful
to keep your life simple,

00:43:06.640 --> 00:43:12.210 align:middle line:84%
because the kingdom
of heaven is within.

00:43:12.210 --> 00:43:15.300 align:middle line:84%
>> I think more and more,
conscious business owners have

00:43:15.300 --> 00:43:18.570 align:middle line:84%
to start thinking in terms of,
there's enough for everyone.

00:43:18.570 --> 00:43:20.400 align:middle line:84%
More often than not,
there are solutions.

00:43:20.400 --> 00:43:22.800 align:middle line:84%
There are ways to
be more inclusive.

00:43:22.800 --> 00:43:26.250 align:middle line:84%
You can find that, hey, if I'm
doing hypnosis and hypnotherapy

00:43:26.250 --> 00:43:28.680 align:middle line:84%
and all sorts of wonderful
stuff and there's

00:43:28.680 --> 00:43:30.370 align:middle line:84%
someone else who
does it near me,

00:43:30.370 --> 00:43:33.010 align:middle line:84%
well, why do I have to
see them as a competitor?

00:43:33.010 --> 00:43:34.140 align:middle line:90%
Why not introduce myself?

00:43:34.140 --> 00:43:37.490 align:middle line:84%
Why not connect and think about,
how can we benefit each other?

00:43:37.490 --> 00:43:40.110 align:middle line:84%
There is enough of
the resources, money,

00:43:40.110 --> 00:43:43.380 align:middle line:84%
people around that if you
have a good product, if you

00:43:43.380 --> 00:43:47.200 align:middle line:84%
have a good service,
there's enough for everyone.

00:43:47.200 --> 00:43:49.630 align:middle line:84%
>> John Templeton
put it so simply.

00:43:49.630 --> 00:43:53.760 align:middle line:84%
He said, the way to get wealthy
is to make others wealthy.

00:43:53.760 --> 00:43:56.320 align:middle line:84%
But I kind of think
on this planet,

00:43:56.320 --> 00:43:58.900 align:middle line:90%
there has been progress made.

00:43:58.900 --> 00:44:03.820 align:middle line:84%
And we do take two steps forward
and then sometimes a huge step

00:44:03.820 --> 00:44:09.400 align:middle line:84%
back as the old systems
are thrashing out

00:44:09.400 --> 00:44:12.940 align:middle line:90%
fighting for survival.

00:44:12.940 --> 00:44:16.690 align:middle line:84%
And in the long run, I
would think the world view

00:44:16.690 --> 00:44:21.430 align:middle line:84%
based on love and partnership,
working it out with everybody,

00:44:21.430 --> 00:44:25.580 align:middle line:84%
realizing we are
one global family.

00:44:25.580 --> 00:44:28.030 align:middle line:84%
>> We're in some ways,
experiencing a dark time.

00:44:28.030 --> 00:44:30.850 align:middle line:84%
In some ways, we're
experiencing a renaissance.

00:44:30.850 --> 00:44:34.000 align:middle line:84%
And so there are some threats
to our existence right now.

00:44:34.000 --> 00:44:35.620 align:middle line:84%
But we also have
more and more people

00:44:35.620 --> 00:44:37.703 align:middle line:84%
who are paying attention,
and more and more people

00:44:37.703 --> 00:44:40.780 align:middle line:84%
who are looking for
solutions in areas

00:44:40.780 --> 00:44:42.120 align:middle line:90%
that we didn't look before.

00:44:42.120 --> 00:44:45.880 align:middle line:90%


00:44:45.880 --> 00:44:48.790 align:middle line:84%
Get out there and do
something nice for somebody.

00:44:48.790 --> 00:44:51.250 align:middle line:84%
And don't expect
anything in return.

00:44:51.250 --> 00:44:52.540 align:middle line:90%
Be kind.

00:44:52.540 --> 00:44:53.980 align:middle line:90%
People need it.

00:44:53.980 --> 00:44:57.940 align:middle line:84%
If we remember that the
people who we complain about

00:44:57.940 --> 00:45:01.030 align:middle line:84%
are human, that underneath
their beliefs and ideologies,

00:45:01.030 --> 00:45:04.180 align:middle line:84%
they're human beings,
it opens up our ability

00:45:04.180 --> 00:45:07.370 align:middle line:90%
to hear one another.

00:45:07.370 --> 00:45:10.850 align:middle line:84%
>> Sometimes we buy into
the materialistic world.

00:45:10.850 --> 00:45:12.580 align:middle line:84%
And we think that
we have no power.

00:45:12.580 --> 00:45:14.980 align:middle line:90%
We think that we're victims.

00:45:14.980 --> 00:45:18.400 align:middle line:84%
But actually, there's a great
deal more power in each of us

00:45:18.400 --> 00:45:22.210 align:middle line:84%
and all of us together
collectively than most of us

00:45:22.210 --> 00:45:25.030 align:middle line:90%
ever realize.

00:45:25.030 --> 00:45:27.250 align:middle line:84%
It's up to all of us
to encourage ourselves

00:45:27.250 --> 00:45:32.110 align:middle line:84%
and one another to maintain
that sense of who we really are.

00:45:32.110 --> 00:45:34.630 align:middle line:84%
Because I believe very
strongly that this

00:45:34.630 --> 00:45:38.050 align:middle line:84%
is the time in our
world history where

00:45:38.050 --> 00:45:40.900 align:middle line:84%
it's more important than
ever before that people

00:45:40.900 --> 00:45:44.095 align:middle line:90%
recognize this.

00:45:44.095 --> 00:45:46.720 align:middle line:84%
>> I think for those people who
don't settle down their nervous

00:45:46.720 --> 00:45:49.120 align:middle line:84%
system with meditation,
who don't have a spiritual

00:45:49.120 --> 00:45:53.530 align:middle line:84%
or creative practice, their
mind is constantly traveling

00:45:53.530 --> 00:45:56.020 align:middle line:84%
into the past, into the
future, and into other

00:45:56.020 --> 00:45:57.430 align:middle line:90%
people's business.

00:45:57.430 --> 00:45:59.680 align:middle line:84%
And when that
happens, they're not

00:45:59.680 --> 00:46:02.260 align:middle line:84%
present for themselves
and the world that's

00:46:02.260 --> 00:46:05.740 align:middle line:90%
being revealed to them.

00:46:05.740 --> 00:46:09.820 align:middle line:84%
A zen master might say,
show me the future.

00:46:09.820 --> 00:46:11.370 align:middle line:90%
Show me your past.

00:46:11.370 --> 00:46:14.920 align:middle line:90%
And there's no way to do it.

00:46:14.920 --> 00:46:17.380 align:middle line:84%
Those questions,
they stop the mind.

00:46:17.380 --> 00:46:18.970 align:middle line:84%
Your mind will
gyrate a little bit,

00:46:18.970 --> 00:46:21.880 align:middle line:84%
and then eventually,
it settles down.

00:46:21.880 --> 00:46:27.490 align:middle line:84%
We dive into the
source of everything.

00:46:27.490 --> 00:46:29.620 align:middle line:84%
We started naming some
of the qualities of it.

00:46:29.620 --> 00:46:31.130 align:middle line:90%
It's eternal.

00:46:31.130 --> 00:46:32.590 align:middle line:90%
It's ever present.

00:46:32.590 --> 00:46:34.930 align:middle line:90%
It's intelligent.

00:46:34.930 --> 00:46:37.000 align:middle line:84%
That's the
transcendence, is when

00:46:37.000 --> 00:46:40.300 align:middle line:84%
we lose track of time and
space and we transcend

00:46:40.300 --> 00:46:43.210 align:middle line:90%
the element of materialism.

00:46:43.210 --> 00:46:46.150 align:middle line:84%
But we can't just go
there because we want to.

00:46:46.150 --> 00:46:48.520 align:middle line:84%
Will doesn't have
much to do with it.

00:46:48.520 --> 00:46:51.190 align:middle line:84%
You cannot will your
mind to stop thinking.

00:46:51.190 --> 00:46:54.640 align:middle line:84%
You cannot will desires
to be made manifest.

00:46:54.640 --> 00:46:59.720 align:middle line:90%
You cannot will enlightenment.

00:46:59.720 --> 00:47:00.580 align:middle line:90%
You can't will it.

00:47:00.580 --> 00:47:04.060 align:middle line:84%
It just happens on its
own accord, spontaneously.

00:47:04.060 --> 00:47:05.980 align:middle line:84%
You have to be present
and here it comes.

00:47:05.980 --> 00:47:08.640 align:middle line:90%


00:47:08.640 --> 00:47:11.520 align:middle line:84%
That's how I navigate life
from, with faith, patience,

00:47:11.520 --> 00:47:13.630 align:middle line:90%
and grace.

00:47:13.630 --> 00:47:15.378 align:middle line:84%
>> But we sometimes
get a feeling, like,

00:47:15.378 --> 00:47:16.920 align:middle line:84%
there's something
else going on here,

00:47:16.920 --> 00:47:19.700 align:middle line:84%
that there is something
much more connected.

00:47:19.700 --> 00:47:24.270 align:middle line:84%
That in a very real sense,
we're sharing the same dream.

00:47:24.270 --> 00:47:27.490 align:middle line:84%
And so I recognize that I'm,
in some ways, playing a role.

00:47:27.490 --> 00:47:30.070 align:middle line:84%
But who I really am
is so much bigger,

00:47:30.070 --> 00:47:31.910 align:middle line:90%
so much more mysterious.

00:47:31.910 --> 00:47:32.710 align:middle line:90%
It's eternal.

00:47:32.710 --> 00:47:33.640 align:middle line:90%
It's infinite.

00:47:33.640 --> 00:47:34.840 align:middle line:90%
It's timeless.

00:47:34.840 --> 00:47:37.990 align:middle line:90%
It's connected to everything.

00:47:37.990 --> 00:47:40.180 align:middle line:84%
Then there's this
collaboration, a symphony

00:47:40.180 --> 00:47:43.250 align:middle line:84%
of all these different,
harmonious pieces,

00:47:43.250 --> 00:47:45.730 align:middle line:84%
each of us playing a
part of the overall song

00:47:45.730 --> 00:47:49.560 align:middle line:84%
and that this is the so-called
music of the spheres,

00:47:49.560 --> 00:47:53.740 align:middle line:84%
that it's our consciousness
that creates all of this.

00:47:53.740 --> 00:47:56.290 align:middle line:84%
And when we get there,
then that is oneness.

00:47:56.290 --> 00:47:58.700 align:middle line:84%
Because everything's
back together again,

00:47:58.700 --> 00:48:02.370 align:middle line:84%
but in such a way that we don't
know what we're looking at.

00:48:02.370 --> 00:48:04.330 align:middle line:90%
>> And we never actually know.

00:48:04.330 --> 00:48:07.520 align:middle line:84%
We hope we're getting
closer to understanding it.

00:48:07.520 --> 00:48:10.390 align:middle line:84%
But I sometimes suspect
that as humans, we

00:48:10.390 --> 00:48:13.270 align:middle line:84%
don't have the capacity
to actually understand

00:48:13.270 --> 00:48:15.290 align:middle line:90%
what's going on.

00:48:15.290 --> 00:48:17.350 align:middle line:84%
And I see this
reflected a little bit

00:48:17.350 --> 00:48:20.800 align:middle line:84%
when you have a mystic who
can go into mystical states.

00:48:20.800 --> 00:48:23.570 align:middle line:84%
They come back with a conviction
that, I understand it now.

00:48:23.570 --> 00:48:24.370 align:middle line:90%
I got it.

00:48:24.370 --> 00:48:25.840 align:middle line:90%
And say, well, tell me.

00:48:25.840 --> 00:48:26.680 align:middle line:90%
What is it?

00:48:26.680 --> 00:48:28.960 align:middle line:84%
And their response
is, it's ineffable.

00:48:28.960 --> 00:48:30.860 align:middle line:90%
I cannot describe it.

00:48:30.860 --> 00:48:33.430 align:middle line:84%
And the reason is that
language at the everyday level

00:48:33.430 --> 00:48:36.640 align:middle line:84%
is not capable of describing
what's actually going on.

00:48:36.640 --> 00:48:39.730 align:middle line:84%
Some mystics will say that they
come out of the mystical state.

00:48:39.730 --> 00:48:41.830 align:middle line:84%
And then they see the
world in a new way.

00:48:41.830 --> 00:48:44.500 align:middle line:84%
And everything is exactly
